winning_structure.name: UBX-MON-PATCH
winning_structure.description: This message reports information about patches installed and currently enabled on the receiver. It does not report on patches installed and then disabled. An enabled patch is considered active when the receiver executes from the code space where the patch resides on. For example, a ROM patch is reported active only when the system runs from ROM.

fields.name: version
fields.description: Message version (0x0001 for this version)

fields.name: nEntries
fields.description: Total number of reported patches

fields.name: patchInfo
fields.description: Status information about the reported patch

bits.name: location
bits.description: Indicates where the patch is stored. 0: eFuse, 1: ROM, 2: BBR, 3: file system

fields.name: comparatorNumber
fields.description: The number of the comparator

fields.name: patchAddress
fields.description: The address that is targeted by the patch

fields.name: patchData
fields.description: The data that is inserted at the patchAddress
